wp set password "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
===============================================================

NAME
----

wp set password - Updates the user's password with a new encrypted one.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Updates the user's password with a new encrypted one.

For integration with other applications, this function can be
overwritten to instead use the other package password checking
algorithm. @uses \$wpdb WordPress database object for queries @uses
wp\_hash\_password() Used to encrypt the user's password before passing
to the database

USAGE
-----

` <?php wp_set_password( $password, $user_id ) ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$password` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The plaintext new user password
    Default: *None*

 `$user_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) User ID
    Default: *None*

EXAMPLES
--------

Below is an example showing how to update a user's password

    <?php
    $user_id = 1;
    $password = 'HelloWorld';
    wp_set_password( $password, $user_id );
    ?>

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

wp\_set\_password() is located in `wp-includes/pluggable.php`

